00:00:26,277 --> 00:00:31,225
to red light, so when long
wavelength light hits them,

13
00:00:31,225 --> 00:00:33,925
that is from the red end of the spectrum,

14
00:00:33,925 --> 00:00:35,974
they respond by sending a
corresponding electrical

15
00:00:35,974 --> 00:00:38,845
signal to the brain, and
the magnitude of this signal

16
00:00:38,845 --> 00:00:42,305
will depend on how much red
light is present in the light.

17
00:00:42,305 --> 00:00:46,285
Our eyes have three main
kinds of color receptors.

18
00:00:46,285 --> 00:00:48,694
One is sensitive to
the longer wavelengths,

19
00:00:48,694 --> 00:00:52,729
redder light, one for medium
wavelengths, or greener light.

20
00:00:52,729 --> 00:00:55,571
And one for shorter
wavelengths, or the bluer light.

21
00:00:55,571 --> 00:00:58,443
