brain blends signals from

22
00:00:58,443 --> 00:01:01,904
these three receptors
to represent any color.

23
00:01:01,904 --> 00:01:04,284
Colored television, and computer monitors,

24
00:01:04,284 --> 00:01:08,333
borrowed this same idea of
color receptors from our eyes.

25
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:09,924
If you zoom into a computer screen,

26
00:01:09,924 --> 00:01:14,655
you'll see it's made up of
tiny rectangles, or pixels.

27
00:01:14,655 --> 00:01:19,485
Each of which contain a
red, green, and blue region.

28
00:01:19,485 --> 00:01:21,934
To display colors, the monitor illuminates

29
00:01:21,934 --> 00:01:24,755
these three colors accordingly.

30
00:01:24,755 --> 00:01:26,717
To make the screen appear yellow,

31
00:01:26,717 --> 00:01:28,604
the monitor turns on only the red and

32
00:01:28,604 --> 00:01:30,953
green regions in each pixel.

33
00:01:30,953 --> 00:01:33,914
